{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"964fd846-c83e-448e-b1f8-3bc0146ac013","content":"Here's your plan. You have .NET 10 SDK, so here are the concrete steps:\n\n---\n\n### 1. Find the Required Android SDK/NDK Versions\n\nYour MAUI workload pins exact versions. Query them:\n\n```bash\n# Install the MAUI workload (includes Android)\nsudo dotnet workload install maui-android\n\n# Find the exact Android components it expects\ndotnet workload list\ncat /usr/share/dotnet/packs/Microsoft.Android.Sdk.Linux/*/AutoImport.props\n```\n\nOr check the `$(AndroidSdkVersion)` / `$(AndroidNdkVersion)` from the installed workload manifests:\n\n```bash\nfind /usr/share/dotnet/sdk-manifests -name 'WorkloadManifest.json' \\\n  -path '*android*' | xargs cat | grep -i 'version\\|ndk\\|sdk'\n```\n\nThis tells you the **exact** API level, build-tools version, and NDK version.\n\n---\n\n### 2. Install OpenJDK 17\n\n```bash\nsudo apt-get update && sudo apt-get install -y openjdk-17-jdk\nexport JAVA_HOME=/usr/lib/jvm/java-17-openjdk-amd64\n```\n\n(MAUI for Android requires JDK 17.)\n\n---\n\n### 3. Install Android Command-Line Tools\n\n```bash\nexport ANDROID_HOME=$HOME/android-sdk\nmkdir -p \"$ANDROID_HOME/cmdline-tools\"\ncurl -fsSL https://dl.google.com/android/repository/commandlinetools-linux-11076708_latest.zip \\\n  -o /tmp/cmdline-tools.zip\nunzip -q /tmp/cmdline-tools.zip -d \"$ANDROID_HOME/cmdline-tools\"\nmv \"$ANDROID_HOME/cmdline-tools/cmdline-tools\" \"$ANDROID_HOME/cmdline-tools/latest\"\nexport PATH=\"$ANDROID_HOME/cmdline-tools/latest/bin:$PATH\"\n```\n\n---\n\n### 4. Accept Licenses & Install Matching Components\n\nUsing the versions found in **step 1** (example values — yours may differ):\n\n```bash\nyes | sdkmanager --licenses\nsdkmanager \\\n  \"platform-tools\" \\\n  \"platforms;android-35\" \\       # match your workload's target API\n  \"build-tools;35.0.0\"          # match your workload's build-tools\n```\n\nThe NDK is typically auto-resolved by the MAUI SDK; you usually don't need to install it separately.\n\n---\n\n### 5. Build\n\n```bash\nexport ANDROID_HOME=$HOME/android-sdk\nexport JAVA_HOME=/usr/lib/jvm/java-17-openjdk-amd64\n\ndotnet build -f net10.0-android   # or net9.0-android for .NET 9\n# For a signed APK:\ndotnet publish -f net10.0-android -c Release\n```\n\n---\n\n### Key Version-Finding Principle\n\nNever hardcode versions — always derive them from the installed workload manifests (`WorkloadManifest.json`). The Android API level and build-tools version are pinned by the MAUI workload you install, so **install the workload first**, then query it to know what `sdkmanager` packages to fetch.\n\nWant me to actually execute these steps now?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"cd81c31c-2805-4991-9f8d-a6c39eb0a0e8","outputTokens":809},"id":"ad2abd4f-8773-4a42-82b6-c4378c24cad7","timestamp":"2026-04-08T00:48:00.232Z","parentId":"16e0261d-f13b-41d7-a91a-c64ab56357cc"}
